 :poll: /v.,n./ 1. [techspeak] The action of checking the status of an input
line, sensor, or memory location to see if a particular external event has
been registered. 2. To repeatedly call or check with someone: "I keep polling
him, but he's not answering his phone; he must be swapped out." 3. To ask.
"Lunch? I poll for a takeout order daily."